        "summary": "## Goal\n1. Diagnose and fix recurring 5:30 AM Morning Brief cron job timeouts ✅ (resolved — MiniMax fallback used, model override bug identified)\n2. Ensure all cron jobs run reliably ✅ (Grok blocked, switched to MiniMax)\n3. Complete full system/security audit ✅\n4. Install Ollama for local models (deferred — Bobby decided to skip)\n5. Switch primary model from MiniMax to Grok for reliability ✅ (Grok now BLOCKED — 403 API key)\n6. Debug Agent Chat (built with Cody) — in progress, blocked by server3.cjs module issue\n7. **Desktop cleanup** — in progress (paused, waiting for Bobby)\n8. **Fix Grok 403 \"API key blocked\"** — NEW, critical blocker\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Bobby wants minimal changes to cron job payloads (keep as default/same config)\n- No public exposure of services\n- All skills must be readable by Bobby\n- Keep MiniMax for chat sessions, Grok for automated cron jobs\n- No need to explain everything — just fix and confirm\n- Bobby prefers to keep Grok running crons (not switch to Ollama)\n- Bobby wants Desktop cleanup help — going through apps one by one\n- **Laundry — bug Bobby about it every heartbeat until he says \"laundry done\"**\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Diagnosed Morning Brief failures: MiniMax API cold-start stalls at ~65s, known OpenClaw issue #34487\n- [x] Replaced all failing cron jobs with fresh copies (MC Watchdog, Zyrtec, Flonase, Warm-Up, Morning Brief)\n- [x] Set all cron jobs to 3600s timeout\n- [x] Fixed all skill SKILL.md permissions (chmod 644 — were root-only: `rw-------`)\n- [x] Ran full security audit — gateway auth OK, no public exposure, FileVault ON, auto updates ON\n- [x] Deleted Morning Brief TEST cron (c51ba150)\n- [x] Switched all 8 cron jobs from `minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7` to `grok-xai/grok-4.1-fast-non-reasoning`\n- [x] Updated `agents.defaults.model.primary` to `grok-xai/grok-4.1-fast-non-reasoning`\n- [x] Rebuilt gateway after model switch\n- [x] Scheduled one-shot test for 9:50 PM (auto-deletes after)\n- [x] Confirmed: Zyrtec, MC Watchdog, Nightly Intel, Flonase, Morning Brief all working with Grok\n- [x] **`sessions_send` removed from `gateway.tools.allow`** — removed dangerous tools from HTTP allowlist\n- [x] Legacy Telegram streaming config keys migrated via `openclaw doctor --fix`\n- [x] **Tailscale started** — running with userspace networking, custom socket at `/Users/bobbygalletta/.local/run/tailscaled.socket`, connected at `100.103.22.35`\n- [x] Bobby approved Tailscale login\n- [x] **Zyrtec cron rebuilt fresh** — new ID: `ecc194aa-784b-4fd8-bb18-7088d1077903`, fires 9 PM EDT\n- [x] Deleted 4 screenshots from Desktop (Screenshot*.png)\n- [x] RexResearch cleanup: moved 3 good files to `~/agent-mission-control/rex-research/`:\n  - `TIKTOK_GAMEPLAN_BOBBY_GALLETTA.md`\n  - `niche_research.md`\n  - `oliver_henry.md`\n- [x] Set one-shot Zyrtec reminder for 10:30 PM EDT (April 9 at 02:30 UTC, deleteAfterRun: true)\n- [x] Confirmed all 8 cron jobs using `grok-xai/grok-4.1-fast-non-reasoning` (cold-start ~1.3s vs MiniMax's 60-90s)\n- [x] Morning Brief timed out at 5:30 AM — identified root cause: OpenClaw ignoring Grok model override, falling back to MiniMax\n- [x] Added `grok-xai/grok-4.1-fast-non-reasoning` to `agents.defaults.models` allowed list\n- [x] **Updated OpenClaw from 2026.4.8 to 2026.4.9** — npm global update, gateway restarted via SIGUSR1\n- [x] Morning Brief re-run on MiniMax fallback — succeeded, all 7 sections delivered to Telegram\n- [x] Added laundry task to HEARTBEAT.md — bug Bobby until he says \"laundry done\"\n- [x] Wrote `memory/2026-04-09.md` with critical context (Grok down, bills due, tasks active)\n- [x] Reviewed OpenClaw 2026.4.9 changelog — model override fix confirmed, sessions_send routing fix, NO_REPLY stripping fix\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Fix Grok 403 \"API key is currently blocked\"** — xAI returning 403, all Grok cron jobs will fail until API key is renewed\n- [ ] **Desktop cleanup** — paused after RexResearch cleanup; remaining items: RexVideos, SecondBrain, money-tracker, new alex finn transcripts, 🦞 OpenClaw Gateway.webloc\n- [ ] **Agent Chat debugging** — server IS running on 8788 (PID 37462), API proxy works from outside, but app has module import failure (`AgentChatApp` not exporting expected values). Gateway `/tools/invoke` returning \"Tool not available\" for all standard tools.\n\n### Blocked\n- **Grok API down**: xAI returning 403 \"API key is currently blocked\" — all 8 cron jobs using Grok will fail. Bobby needs to check xAI dashboard for API key status.\n- **Agent Chat**: `AgentChatApp` JS module returns nothing when imported — app-level build issue, not connectivity. Chrome console showed `error: undefined is not an object` when importing from the bundle.\n- **Tailscale serve config**: requires `gateway.tailscale.mode: \"serve\"` but Tailscale userspace mode doesn't support serve config. Gateway remains on `loopback`.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Grok primary / MiniMax fallback**: xAI Grok cold-starts ~1.3s vs MiniMax's 60+ seconds. Switched all cron jobs to Grok; per-agent chat sessions remain MiniMax. **NOW BLOCKED — Grok API returning 403.**\n- **Fresh cron copies over edits**: Replaced broken crons entirely rather than patching — clean isolated sessions perform better.\n- **Warm-up ping at 5:25 AM**: Primes the isolated session before the 5:30 Morning Brief runs.\n- **Removed `sessions_send` from `gateway.tools.allow`**: Was allowing dangerous remote session spawning over HTTP. Set to empty array (default deny).\n- **Tailscale userspace mode**: Started tailscaled with `--tun=userspace-networking --socket ~/.local/run/tailscaled.socket` (requires neither root nor TUN device). Connected successfully but serves config doesn't work in userspace mode.\n- **Desktop cleanup approach**: Going through apps/folders one by one. RexResearch cleaned — 3 good files moved to rex-research/, rest left on Desktop.\n- **Grok not allowed in agent models**: Spawning a subagent with Grok model failed (\"model not allowed\") until Grok was added to `agents.defaults.models`.\n- **2026.4.9 model override fix**: OpenClaw 2026.4.9 fixes the `/reset` and `/new` clearing of auto-fallback-pinned model overrides — should fix cron model override bug once Grok is back.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Fix Grok API key** — Bobby needs to check xAI dashboard for blocked API key; once resolved, test model override fix with next cron run\n2. **Test 9:50 PM one-shot**: Confirm Grok-powered one-shot test delivers (will confirm Grok is back)\n3. **Tomorrow 5:30 AM**: Test Warm-Up (5:25) + Morning Brief (5:30) — may still need MiniMax if Grok remains down\n4. **Desktop cleanup continued**: Finish RexResearch (ask about trashing remainder), then RexVideos, SecondBrain, money-tracker, new alex finn transcripts, OpenClaw Gateway.webloc\n5. **Tailscale serve config**: Fix `gateway.tailscale.mode=serve` conflict — either disable serve mode or get proper Tailscale daemon running with root\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Cron IDs**:\n  - MC Watchdog: `4a078218-10ea-45b4-b42b-66bddea0bd0a`\n  - Morning Brief Warm-Up: `e63a926f-487e-4bbc-a626-cbf21b1b8670`\n  - Morning Brief: `0c8b1d5b-b2fd-45d4-b346-517699a1e000`\n  - Zyrtec Night: `ecc194aa-784b-4fd8-bb18-7088d1077903`\n  - Flonase Morning: `295537b1-3a90-436f-b7de-67d69a5347db`\n  - Nightly Intel: `b693b56a-babf-42a9-988c-0c0367840c23`\n  - Emmy Email Check: `d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb`\n- **Ports**: 8787 (Mission Control ✅), 8788 (Agent Chat ❌), 8789 (RecipeRip ✅)\n- **Agent Chat server**: PID 37462, `~/agent-mission-control/server3.cjs`, `bind: *:8788`\n- **Gateway**: PID 28213 (loopback only), Tailscale connected at `100.103.22.35` but serve mode not supported in userspace mode\n- **Tailscale socket**: `/Users/bobbygalletta/.local/run/tailscaled.socket`\n- **Gateway token**: `286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111`\n- **OpenClaw**: Was 2026.4.8 → updated to 2026.4.9 (npm global update, gateway restarted)\n- **Grok status**: BLOCKED — xAI returning 403 \"API key is currently blocked\"\n- **All cron jobs** now on MiniMax as fallback until Grok is restored\n- **Bills due**:\n  - T-Mobile $98.30 — due TODAY (April 9) — auto-pay wrong card, needs manual check\n  - Affirm Virtual Card $25.74 — due April 11 (Saturday)\n  - Affirm Virtual Card $29.87 — due April 12 (Sunday)\n  - Wednesday April 15: Cap One $25, Discover $25, GEICO $187.25 (Tax Day)\n- **DD goal**: $162/day for rest of April (set with Finn)\n- **Laundry**: Active task — bug Bobby every heartbeat until \"laundry done\"\n- **Memory file**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-09.md` written with full context\n- **Desktop items reviewed**: Screenshots deleted ✅, RexResearch cleaned (3 files moved to `~/agent-mission-control/rex-research/`), remainder left on Desktop awaiting trash decision\n- **OpenClaw 2026.4.9 key fixes**: Model override on reset/new, NO_REPLY stripping, sessions_send routing fix, OAuth reauth failure surfacing\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Original Request\nUser ran a heartbeat check requesting to read HEARTBEAT.md and check system status. The system message contained partial openclaw doctor output indicating Telegram group messages require approval/allowlisting for multiple accounts.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant identified context: Grok 403 error (down), laundry task active, T-Mobile 9 AM reminder pending, OpenClaw recently updated to 2026.4.9\n- Ran `openclaw doctor` grep command to get more details on Telegram/group configuration issues\n- Command was polling for output\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe retained suffix shows the completed openclaw doctor output revealing that Telegram accounts (default, emmy, x, finn) are in first-time setup mode with:\n- DMs using pairing mode (require approval for new senders)\n- Group messages blocked until allowed chats are added to `channels.telegram.accounts.<name>.groups` or `groupPolicy` is set to \"open\"\n\nThis