        "summary": "## Goal\n1. Diagnose and fix recurring 5:30 AM Morning Brief cron job timeouts ✅ (resolved)\n2. Ensure all cron jobs run reliably ✅ (resolved — switched to MiniMax)\n3. Complete full system/security audit ✅\n4. Install Ollama for local models (deferred — Bobby decided to skip)\n5. Fix Grok 403 \"API key blocked\" ✅ (key was blocked by xAI; new working key obtained)\n6. **Get grok-4.1 enabled on Bobby's xAI team** — delegated to Bobby (emailed support)\n7. **Desktop cleanup** — paused, waiting for Bobby\n8. **Enable Dreaming for all agents** ✅ (memory-core plugin enabled globally, 3 AM daily)\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Bobby wants minimal changes to cron job payloads\n- No public exposure of services\n- All skills must be readable by Bobby\n- **Keep all crons on MiniMax for now** — until xAI enables grok-4.1 on Bobby's team\n- No need to explain everything — just fix and confirm\n- **Laundry — bug Bobby until \"laundry done\"** ✅ (LAUNDRY DONE — removed reminder cron)\n- Bobby wants grok-4.1 specifically (not 4.20 — too expensive)\n- Bobby approved enabling Dreaming for entire team\n- Bobby wants Emmy to prepare but approve any outbound emails before sending\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Diagnosed Morning Brief failures: MiniMax API cold-start stalls at ~65s, known OpenClaw issue #34487\n- [x] Replaced all failing cron jobs with fresh copies (MC Watchdog, Zyrtec, Flonase, Warm-Up, Morning Brief)\n- [x] Set all cron jobs to 3600s timeout\n- [x] Fixed all skill SKILL.md permissions (chmod 644)\n- [x] Ran full security audit — gateway auth OK, no public exposure, FileVault ON, auto updates ON\n- [x] Deleted Morning Brief TEST cron (c51ba150)\n- [x] Switched all 8 cron jobs from MiniMax to `grok-xai/grok-4.1-fast-non-reasoning`\n- [x] Updated `agents.defaults.model.primary` to `grok-xai/grok-4.1-fast-non-reasoning`\n- [x] Rebuilt gateway after model switch\n- [x] Removed `sessions_send` from `gateway.tools.allow`\n- [x] Legacy Telegram streaming config keys migrated\n- [x] Tailscale started (userspace networking)\n- [x] Deleted 4 screenshots from Desktop\n- [x] RexResearch cleanup: moved 3 good files to `~/agent-mission-control/rex-research/`\n- [x] **Updated OpenClaw from 2026.4.8 → 2026.4.9** — npm global update, gateway restarted via SIGUSR1\n- [x] **Grok 403 FIXED** — old key blocked by xAI; Bobby provided new key: `xai-xMPUmMTwzAKdvKL6mNm0AkufZ9ZOoeOADhg5f9OCJtQIypMRPP1fogrhmedjLkuwSIONlm9U3jAXq5mB`\n- [x] Updated both `xai` and `grok-xai` providers in OpenClaw with new working key; gateway hot-reloaded\n- [x] Bobby missed Morning Brief (5:30 AM timeout) — re-ran on MiniMax manually, delivered ~5:52 AM\n- [x] Bobby missed Flonase (9 AM — failed due to Grok blocked) — took Flonase manually ~10 AM\n- [x] **RecipeRip fully fixed** — server was missing dotenv; fixed code, added XAI_API_KEY to LaunchAgent (`com.bobby.missioncontrol.api.plist`) inline env var; API tested ✅\n- [x] Updated `~/.env` (at `~/agent-mission-control/.env`) with new working xAI key\n- [x] Updated `com.bobby.missioncontrol.api.plist` with inline `XAI_API_KEY` env var; LaunchAgent restarted\n- [x] Bobby confirmed: new xAI key has access to all models and endpoints — grok-4.1 should work but xAI Responses API returning \"Model not found\"\n- [x] **Root cause identified**: Bobby's xAI team (`09c1d36c-fb69-4d0f-9c0c-f274269a8a39`) doesn't have grok-4.1 models enabled on the Responses API endpoint. Chat Completions API (`/v1/chat/completions`) works with `grok-3`, `grok-4`, `grok-4-fast-non-reasoning`; Responses API (`/v1/responses`) returns \"Model not found\" for ALL grok-4.1 variants\n- [x] Bobby emailed xAI support requesting grok-4.1 enablement on his team; Emmy drafted email on Bobby's behalf (Bobby approved and sent manually)\n- [x] **Switched all 8 cron jobs + laundry reminder to MiniMax** — grok-4.1 blocked on xAI's end\n- [x] Switched 4 PM laundry reminder to `xai/grok-4-fast-non-reasoning` for testing; Bobby then said keep MiniMax\n- [x] Laundry done — removed 30-min reminder cron (`16c8d861-7213-4b20-a791-3234b831ba1b`); set new 4 PM reminder (`0eb98b1e-0768-4044-aec3-2282c70434e4`) which Bobby will dismiss when laundry is fully done\n- [x] Full systems check run — OpenClaw ✅, Tailscale ✅, MC API (3001) ✅, Agent Chat (8788) ✅, RecipeRip API ✅\n- [x] `lossless-claw` extension flagged as untracked local code — needs trust pin\n- [x] OpenClaw Node (macOS companion app daemon) exit code -9 — not critical\n- [x] RecipeRip frontend (port 8789) blocked — `server3.cjs` can't bind (port 8788 already in use by individual vite server); API on port 3001 works fine\n- [x] Bobby approved enabling Dreaming for entire team — enabled via `plugins.entries.memory-core.config.dreaming: { enabled: true, frequency: \"0 3 * * *\", timezone: \"America/New_York\" }` in global config; all 10 agent workspaces covered; first dreams fire tonight at 3 AM EDT\n- [x] Updated memory/2026-04-09.md with all resolutions\n- [x] Bobby's xAI team ID: `09c1d36c-fb69-4d0f-9c0c-f274269a8a39`\n- [x] Bobby wants grok-4.1 (not 4.20 — too expensive: $3/M input, $15/M output vs $0.20/M input, $0.50/M output for 4.1)\n- [x] Bobby asked about OpenClaw 2026.4.9 features: model override bug fix, sessions_send routing fix, NO_REPLY stripping, OAuth reauth surfacing, faster isolated session startup, improved cron error diagnostics\n- [x] Bobby asked about \"Dream\" feature: OpenClaw Dreaming — background memory consolidation (Light → Deep → REM phases); opt-in; REM backfill + Diary Timeline UI; per-workspace Dream Diary; runs 3 AM nightly; enabled globally for all 10 agent workspaces\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **xAI grok-4.1 enablement** — Bobby emailed support; waiting for xAI to enable grok-4.1-fast-non-reasoning on team `09c1d36c-fb69-4d0f-9c0c-f274269a8a39`\n- [ ] **Desktop cleanup** — paused; remaining: RexVideos, SecondBrain, money-tracker, new alex finn transcripts, 🦞 OpenClaw Gateway.webloc\n\n### Blocked\n- ~~**Grok API down**: xAI returning 403~~ ✅ RESOLVED — new working key\n- ~~**RecipeRip missing dotenv**~~ ✅ RESOLVED — LaunchAgent now passes XAI_API_KEY inline\n- ~~**Agent Chat debugging**~~ — not actively being worked\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **All crons on MiniMax for now**: grok-4.1 not accessible via xAI Responses API for Bobby's team; grok-4 too expensive ($3/$15 vs $0.20/$0.50 per 1M tokens for 4.1); grok-4-fast-non-reasoning works via Chat Completions but is still one generation back\n- **New working xAI key**: `xai-xMPUmMTwzAKdvKL6mNm0AkufZ9ZOoeOADhg5f9OCJtQIypMRPP1fogrhmedjLkuwSIONlm9U3jAXq5mB`; works for Chat Completions (grok-3, grok-4); blocked on Responses API for grok-4.1 models\n- **Bobby emails xAI support directly**: Team ID `09c1d36c-fb69-4d0f-9c0c-f274269a8a39` needs grok-4.1 enabled on Responses API\n- **Dreaming enabled globally**: memory-core plugin config covers all 10 agent workspaces; cron at 3 AM Eastern daily; Dream Diary visible in Gateway Dreams tab\n- **RecipeRip served via API only**: Port 8789 frontend blocked by port conflict; port 3001 API works correctly\n- **Fresh cron copies over edits**: Replaced broken crons entirely rather than patching — clean isolated sessions perform better\n- **Removed `sessions_send` from `gateway.tools.allow`**: Dangerous remote session spawning blocked from HTTP allowlist\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Wait for xAI response** on grok-4.1 enablement (team `09c1d36c-fb69-4d0f-9c0c-f274269a8a39`); once enabled, switch crons from MiniMax to `xai/grok-4.1-fast-non-reasoning`\n2. **Test 4 PM laundry reminder** (cron ID `0eb98b1e-0768-4044-aec3-2282c70434e4`) — Bobby dismisses when laundry fully done\n3. **Tonight's crons**: Zyrtec at 9 PM ✅, Nightly Intel at 10:26 PM ✅ (all on MiniMax, should fire normally)\n4. **Dreaming fires tonight at 3 AM**: All 10 agents will consolidate memories; review Dream Diary in Gateway tomorrow\n5. **Desktop cleanup continued**: Ask Bobby about trashing RexResearch remainder, then RexVideos, SecondBrain, money-tracker, alex finn transcripts, OpenClaw Gateway.webloc\n6. **Tomorrow 5:30 AM**: Morning Brief + Warm-Up on MiniMax (Grok still down on 4.1)\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Cron IDs**:\n  - MC Watchdog: `4a078218-10ea-45b4-b42b-66bddea0bd0a` → MiniMax ✅\n  - Morning Brief Warm-Up: `e63a926f-487e-4bbc-a626-cbf21b1b8670` → MiniMax ✅\n  - Morning Brief: `0c8b1d5b-b2fd-45d4-b346-517699a1e000` → MiniMax ✅\n  - Zyrtec Night: `ecc194aa-784b-4fd8-bb18-7088d1077903` → MiniMax ✅\n  - Flonase Morning: `295537b1-3a90-436f-b7de-67d69a5347db` → MiniMax ✅\n  - Nightly Intel: `b693b56a-babf-42a9-988c-0c0367840c23` → MiniMax ✅\n  - Emmy Email Check: `d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb` → MiniMax ✅\n  - Laundry 4PM: `0eb98b1e-0768-4044-aec3-2282c70434e4` → MiniMax, deleteAfterRun ✅\n  - Weather Cache Refresh: `720739ac-4722-437b-8271-b7c1189c905c` → MiniMax ✅\n- **Ports**: 8787 (MC frontend ✅), 8788 (Agent Chat ✅), 8789 (RecipeRip frontend ❌ — port conflict), 3001 (RecipeRip API ✅)\n- **Gateway**: PID on loopback, Tailscale at `100.103.22.35` but serve mode not supported in userspace\n- **Gateway token**: `286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111`\n- **Tailscale socket**: `/Users/bobbygalletta/.local/run/tailsqd.socket`\n- **OpenClaw**: 2026.4.9\n- **Working xAI key**: `xai-xMPUmMTwzAKdvKL6mNm0AkufZ9ZOoeOADhg5f9OCJtQIypMRPP1fogrhmedjLkuwSIONlm9U3jAXq5mB`\n- **xAI team ID**: `09c1d36c-fb69-4d0f-9c0c-f274269a8a39`\n- **Agent workspaces**: `~/.openclaw/workspace*` — all 10 agents have separate workspaces with MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, HEARTBEAT.md, etc.\n- **Dreaming**: `plugins.entries.memory-core.config.dreaming.enabled: true`, frequency `0 3 * * *` America/New_York; all workspaces covered\n- **LaunchAgent**: `com.bobby.missioncontrol.api.plist` updated with inline `XAI_API_KEY` env var; server PID 26014, port 3001\n- **Bills due**:\n  - T-Mobile $98.30 — due TODAY April 9 (auto-pay issue — Bobby checking)\n  - Affirm $25.74 — due April 11 (Saturday)\n  - Affirm $29.87 — due April 12 (Sunday)\n  - April 15: Cap One $25, Discover $25, GEICO $187.25 (Tax Day)\n- **DD goal**: $162/day for rest of April\n- **Laundry**: Done — in dryer; 4 PM reminder still pending (Bobby dismisses when done)\n- **Memory**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-09.md` — updated with full Grok/RecipeRip resolutions and xAI team ID\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser reported the gateway restart failed with \"Gateway: agents.dreaming failed\" error after applying a config patch for enabling Dreaming.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Ran `openclaw doctor --non-interactive` → 0 errors found (no dreaming errors)\n- Checked gateway logs at `~/.openclaw/logs/`\n- Found \"gateway closed (1000)\" errors in `gateway.err.log` - multiple Telegram and WebSocket connection failures\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The system health check passes (0 errors from doctor)\n- Gateway error logs show connection closures (code 1000 = normal closure) for Telegram bot and WebSocket clients attempting to connect\n- This appears to be a connectivity issue where clients can't reach the gateway, not necessarily a Dreaming config problem\n- Need to continue investigating why gateway is closing connections and whether it's actually running\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-08.md\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/dreaming.md\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md\n~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n~/.openclaw/skills/morning-brief/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-09.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Library/LaunchAgents/com.bobby.missioncontrol.api.plist\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/.env\n</modified-files>",
